From e6b09345174d80942cab61c87a80cb7ef6d7805f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mark Cave-Ayland <mark.cave-ayland@ilande.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 20 Jun 2025 13:37:16 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] all: update from using internal bool implementation to
 stdbool

Since the bool type was included in the C99 standard nearly 30 years ago, it
is fairly safe to say that all modern compilers contain support for stdbool.

Remove the internal bool implementation from shared/types.h and then switch
over to using stdbool instead. The changes are fairly simple: change TRUE
and FALSE to lower case, and then remove the BOOLVAL() and INVERSE() macros
which are now no longer required.

Signed-off-by: Mark Cave-Ayland <mark.cave-ayland@ilande.co.uk>
